# Tailwind styling

- Tailwind **v4** via `app/globals.css` (`@import "tailwindcss"`, `@theme inline`).
- No legacy `tailwind.config` unless added later.
- **No hardcoded hex** in components — use semantic tokens or `lumina-*`.

## Type scale

All `--text-*` tokens are **+2px** vs Tailwind defaults (defined in `globals.css`). Body text inherits `--text-base` (18px).

## Color palette

### Neutrals

| Token | Light | Dark | Usage |
|-------|-------|------|-------|
| `background` | `#F7FAF8` | `#032A5A` | Page background |
| `surface` | `#FFFFFF` | `#04316D` | Cards, inputs |
| `foreground` | `#04316D` | `#EAF5ED` | Headings, body text |
| `muted` | `#47827A` | `#69AA80` | Placeholders, metadata |

### Accents

| Token | Hex | Usage |
|-------|-----|-------|
| `lumina-900` | `#04316D` | Primary buttons, headings, links, focus ring |
| `lumina-700` | `#265973` | Hover states, outline buttons, borders (dark) |
| `lumina-500` | `#47827A` | Input borders, icons, tags |
| `lumina-300` | `#69AA80` | Selected states, success feedback |
| `lumina-100` | `#8AD286` | Badges, focus glow — use sparingly (~5% UI) |

### 80/15/5 split

80% neutrals, 15% lumina-900/700, 5% lumina-300/100.

## Class order

1. Layout → 2. Spacing → 3. Typography → 4. Background/borders → 5. States/responsive

## Reflection UX

- Generous whitespace; no visual clutter.
- `leading-relaxed`, `max-w-prose` for text blocks.
- Soft borders: `border-lumina-500/25`.

## Dark mode

Via `prefers-color-scheme` — tokens switch automatically; no `dark:` needed for base colors.

## Examples

```tsx
<button className="bg-lumina-900 text-surface hover:bg-lumina-700 focus-visible:outline-lumina-900">

<textarea
  className="bg-surface border border-lumina-500/25 text-foreground placeholder:text-muted focus:border-lumina-500 focus:ring-lumina-100/50"
  placeholder="Waar denk je vandaag aan?"
/>
```
